cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing a device to assist visually impaired people in their daily life, which involves interaction between humans and computers.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel obstacle avoiding algorithm that utilizes sensors, which is a common technique in robotics.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the paper mentions the use of depth sensors and AR techniques, which are related to computer vision.
- cs.SD (Sound) is relevant as the paper discusses the development of auditory cues to assist totally blind people.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper addresses a social issue of improving the travelling experience of visually impaired people.
